<P>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#FF0000">*If HTML and/or <A HREF="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/ubbcode.html" target=_blank>UBB Code</A> are enabled, this means you can use HTML and/or UBB Code in your message.</FONT>
<br>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Balcoth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At level 30 I put points into Spec Alteration nothing else, now I am 54 and just noticed my specialization never went up.<P>So now i put one point into each other specialization and spent an hour casting Alterations spells with no skill raises, I cant figure out why i cant get the skills up any one got any ideas?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arachn Noircoeur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you are sure you put one point in each now it should be ok. Just need time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kero</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually, no, he's not fine.  When you first put a point into a skill, it starts off at your current level.  And with Specialization, you will not get one over 50, until each are at least 1.  <P>So he's got alteration at 50.  Which is where it stayed.  Then at 54, he put a point into the rest... the first one got to be 54, the rest are 50.<P>You need to do the reset specialization quest in the Temple of Ro.  Details <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711">here</a></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Amberel-dro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's also possible that you have the same bug as I did.  My specalizations were all stuck at 50, and I couldn't get one past 50(although I was also missing a specalization, it didn't even show up at my guildmaster).  The GM had to get on Amb to reset everything, and then it was fine.  If you do have the same problem, then you'll have to petition and talk to the head GM.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165516" TARGET=_blank>Amb</A><BR><A HREF="http://hossguild.com/" TARGET=_blank>Hoss</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grumbles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I bet it didnt credit Specialize in Abjuration, Divination, Conjuration and Evocation at 54, I'll bet it put them at 30, the level we get the ability to specialize.  You can test this by looking at your skills menu.  I forget the exact ranges but the terms are like "feeble" "very bad" "awful" and so-on.  If I am remembering correctly those run in 10 point blocks, so to check and see if your in trouble or not, look at all your specialize fields.<P>Alteration SHOULD be the highest because it's at 50.  <P>Evo, Div, Conj, Abj should all be tied at whatever term is for 30 points.<P>If one of them is different, and above the level of Alteration, then it's like Kero said, you got credited with 54 points the first time you added a point into whichever skill it was and now you have to go do the reset quest in Temple of Sol.<P>Good luck,<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18964" TARGET=_blank>Grumbles</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arachn Noircoeur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aye, if you put any points after 54 then it's stuck, my mistake.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
